# API Spector — Windsurf Rules

This project uses API Spector for API testing.

## References

When working with test scripts or collection files, read:
- `.windsurf/docs/api-spector-scripting-reference.md` — Full `sp.*` scripting API
- `.windsurf/docs/collection-file-format.md` — Collection and environment file format
- `.windsurf/docs/functional-testing-guide.md` — Functional test patterns
- `.windsurf/docs/security-testing-guide.md` — OWASP API Top 10 test patterns

## Script conventions

- Use `sp.test('name', function() { ... })` for assertions
- Use `sp.expect(value)` with `.to.equal()`, `.to.include()`, `.to.be.a()`, etc.
- Parse body: `const json = sp.response.json();`
- Set variables: `sp.environment.set("key", "value")`
- Use `{{variable}}` in URLs, headers, body, and scripts
